# Simple HTTP tests for file uploads
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
# For deployed version, use: @baseUrl = https://your-app.azurewebsites.net
@courseId = test-course-123
@studentId = test-student-789
@teacherId = test-teacher-101

### Test 1: Create Assignment with Text Only (No Files)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/courses/{{courseId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Simple Text Assignment",
  "description": "This is a test assignment without files",
  "instructions": "Please submit your answer in text format",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31T23:59:59Z",
  "maxPoints": 50,
  "assignmentType": "homework",
  "submissionFormat": "text",
  "createdBy": "{{teacherId}}"
}

### Test 2: Submit Assignment with Text Only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/assignments/YOUR_ASSIGNMENT_ID_HERE/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": "{{studentId}}",
  "studentName": "John Doe",
  "studentEmail": "john.doe@student.edu",
  "submissionText": "This is my text submission for the assignment. I have completed all the required tasks and provided detailed explanations for each step."
}

### Test 3: Get Assignment Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/assignments/YOUR_ASSIGNMENT_ID_HERE

### Test 4: Get All Assignments
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/assignments/

### Test 5: Get Course Assignments
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/courses/{{courseId}}/assignments

### Test 6: Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Test 7: Get Assignment Submissions (Replace with actual assignment ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/assignments/YOUR_ASSIGNMENT_ID_HERE/submissions

### Test 8: Get Submission Details (Replace with actual submission ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/submissions/YOUR_SUBMISSION_ID_HERE

### Test 9: Download Assignment Attachment (Replace with actual IDs and filename)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/assignments/YOUR_ASSIGNMENT_ID_HERE/attachments/YOUR_FILENAME_HERE/download

### Test 10: Download Submission Attachment (Replace with actual IDs and filename)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/submissions/YOUR_SUBMISSION_ID_HERE/attachments/YOUR_FILENAME_HERE/download
